<subSubSection id="9BEE82B5E179D87BFF220752FBBDFD79" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D34BD13EE179D87BFF220752FBBDFD79" blockId="17.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis id="E1800D2CE179D87BFF220752FEE2FDEC" bold="true" box="[199,335,548,573]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Comments.</emphasis>
This species has been collected to date only at the Monfort crusader castle and within a radius of about one kilometer from it, constituting one of the most beautiful sites in 
<collectingCountry id="ABE391AEE179D87BFC350731FBBFFDB1" box="[976,1042,583,608]" name="Israel" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Israel</collectingCountry>
. The locality names originally used and cited on the labels, i.e., “Montfort”, “Monfort”, “Nahal Keziv”, “Nahal Keziv, Monfort” and “N. Keziv” (Nahal, in Hebrew, meaning river or stream) more or less refer to the same site.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
